British Prime Minister Boris Johnson, who tested positive for the coronavirus roughly two weeks ago, has been discharged from the intensive care unit at St. Thomas’ Hospital after receiving oxygen support. “The Prime Minister has been moved this evening from intensive care back to the ward, where he will receive close monitoring during the early phase of his recovery,” Downing Street said in a statement. “He is in extremely good spirits.” The prime minister was hospitalized on Sunday and was transferred to the intensive care unit the following day. Source •Boris Johnson, British PM LONDON - British Prime Minister Boris Johnson has been moved to intensive care in hospital after his coronavirus symptoms "worsened", Downing Street has said. A spokesman said he was moved on the advice of his medical team and is receiving "excellent care". Mr Johnson has asked… April 6, 2020 In "Foreign" By Agency Report Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Prime Minister Boris Johnson has been moved to intensive care in hospital after his coronavirus symptoms worsened, Downing Street has said. A spokesman said he was moved on the advice of his medical team and is receiving excellent care. Mr Johnson had asked… April 7, 2020 In "Foreign" England, Scotland and Wales have recorded 887 more coronavirus deaths today, taking Britain's total to 7,984 as its coronavirus crisis rumbles on. The grim tally is considerably smaller than the devastating 938 announced yesterday but still represents the second biggest surge since the epidemic began almost six weeks ago. NHS… April 9, 2020 In "News"